casebody.data:
No. 153,

Misc.

Gonzalez v. United States. Petitioner pro se. Solicitor General Rankin, Assistant Attorney General Olney, Beatrice Rosenberg and Robert G. Maysack for the United States. Per Curiam:

The motion for leave to proceed in forma pauperis and the petition for writ of certiorari are granted. In light of the memorandum of the Solicitor General and upon our consideration of the entire record, the order is vacated and the cause is remanded to the Court of Appeals for consideration on the merits as a timely appeal under the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure.
